# ============================================================================
# NOTES AND RECOMMENDATIONS - UPDATED FOR EUROPE
# ============================================================================

# 1. ALWAYS set your cloud provider first: cloud_provider = "gcp" or "aws"
# 2. For AWS: Ensure aws_key_name exists in your target region
# 3. For GCP: Ensure gcp_project_id is correct and you have access
# 4. IMPORTANT: Use Europe-compatible machine types for GCP Europe regions:
#    - Use n2-standard-4 instead of n1-standard-4
#    - Use n2-highcpu-8 instead of n1-standard-8
#    - Use e2-standard-4 for budget deployments
# 5. Use spot/preemptible instances for testing to save 60-70% on costs
# 6. Remember to stop instances when not testing to avoid charges
# 7. For production use, restrict SSH access with specific CIDR blocks
# 8. Enable monitoring for production deployments
# 9. Consider using Elastic IP (AWS) for long-term deployments
# 10. Test from multiple geographic locations for comprehensive results
# 11. Monitor cloud billing dashboards to avoid unexpected costs
# 12. europe-north1 (Finland) is the cheapest GCP Europe region

# ============================================================================
# TROUBLESHOOTING - UPDATED
# ============================================================================

# If deployment fails:
# 1. Check cloud provider authentication: aws configure / gcloud auth login
# 2. Verify required variables are set correctly
# 3. Ensure key pairs exist in the target region
# 4. Check quota limits in your cloud account
# 5. Review Terraform error messages for specific issues
# 6. FOR GCP EUROPE: Ensure you're using n2/e2/c2 machine types, not n1 types

# If performance is lower than expected:
# 1. Try different instance types with higher network performance
# 2. Test from multiple geographic locations
# 3. Use parallel connections (-P 4)
# 4. Check client-side network limitations
# 5. Verify enhanced networking is enabled
# 6. For GCP: Consider n2-highcpu-8 or n2-standard-8 for maximum performance

# For SSH connection issues:
# 1. Check security groups/firewall rules allow SSH from your IP
# 2. Verify SSH key pair is correctly configured
# 3. Wait 2-3 minutes after deployment for services to start
# 4. Use cloud console to verify instance is running

# Machine type errors in GCP Europe regions:
# 1. Error "machine type not found" ‚Üí Use n2-standard-4 instead of n1-standard-4
# 2. Error "does not support machine type n1-standard-*" ‚Üí Switch to n2/e2 series
# 3. Check machine type availability: gcloud compute machine-types list --filter="zone:your-zone"
